cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms to teach a computer program how to play video games. This falls under the domain of AI and is the most likely category for this paper.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to train the computer program to play video games. This is a sub-category of AI and is also likely for this paper.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper may discuss the use of computer vision techniques to analyze the game screen and make decisions based on the visual information. This is less likely than the previous two categories, but still possible.
4. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper may discuss the graphics and visual aspects of the video games being played in the Retro Learning Environment. This is less likely than the previous categories, but still possible.
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper may discuss the game theory aspects of playing video games and how the computer program makes decisions based on the game rules and objectives. This is the least likely category, but still possible.
